 an appointment by calling the Career Services office at 312-996-2300 .  Refer to the Hours/Location page for advising hours.        May I make an appointment for the same day I call?         FAQ11   While we do not offer same-day appointments, you may come in during walk-in advising hours for assistance.        If I missed my advising appointment, may I reschedule?         FAQ10   You may reschedule your appointment up to three times. After that you may no longer make appointments, you may only use walk-in advising.        Do I have to meet with the advisor that specializes in my major? Can I meet with a different advisor?         FAQ12   You may choose to meet with a different advisor if you like, but we recommend you first speak with the advisor that specializes in your field if your schedule allows.        Is your office the only career services office?         FAQ13   Depending on your field of study, you may also seek service from other career centers on campus .        Are UIC graduates (alumni) able to use Career Services' services?         FAQ2   UIC Graduates (Alumni) may schedule an career advising appointment at the with a Career Services advisor.  Additionally, UIC Graduates (Alumni) have lifetime access to UIC hosted career / job fairs hosted on-campus unless noted otherwise.  UIC Graduates (Alumni) may attend on-campus career workshops hosted by the UIC Career Services office unless noted otherwise.  Refer to the Alumni page for complete details on alumni access to career services and events.        Are graduates of other University of Illinois institutions (Urbana-Champaign, Springfield) able to use your services?         FAQ4   Unfortunately, our services are limited to University of Illinois at Chicago (UIC) students. Please contact your university’s career services offices for assistance.             Advising Services     How may I get help with interviewing?         FAQ3a        You may get help a variety of ways:   Find self-help resources and training on the Interviews and Networking pages.  Schedule a career advising appointment for advice or drop in for 15-minute advice session during walk-in advising hours (no appointment required).  Check the hours/location page for walk-in advising hours.  Students can log into UICcareers.com to obtain access to the Mock Interview module in which students can tailor and record practice responses to common interview questions.  Further details on how to use the tool can be found on the Interviews page.              How may I get help with my resume, CV, or cover letter?         FAQ4a        You may get help a variety of ways:   Find self-help resources and training on the Resumes, CVs, and Cover Letters page .  Schedule a career advising appointment for advice or drop in for 15-minute resume review during walk-in advising hours (no appointment required).  Check the hours/location page for walk-in advising hours.  Attend an upcoming workshop on resume or cover letter development.              How may I get help with choosing a major and/or thinking about a career?         FAQ5a        You may get help a variety of ways:   Find self-help resources and training on the Career Exploration page .  Schedule a career advising appointment for in depth advice or drop in for 15-minute advising (no appointment required) during walk-in advising hours.  Check the hours/location page for walk-in advising hours.  Attend an upcoming workshop or discussion panel on career topics.              What is a mock interview and how do I schedule it?         FAQ6a                   Students can strengthen their interview skills by scheduling a practice or “mock interview” with a UIC Career Advisor.  Following the practice interview, you will receive feedback about interviewing strengths and areas to improve.UIC Students and Alumni may schedule a mock interview on weekdays between 9:00 am and 4:00 pm (including over breaks) by calling the Career Services office at 312-996-2300 .                 UICcareers     Why should I and how do I log into UICcareers.com?         FAQ1a   UICcareers.com * provides access to employment and internships posted by employers.  It also provides informational updates on upcoming employer events and career events.  To access the site, type in your UIC email address (name@uic.edu) as your username, then hit FORGOT PASSWORD. In a few minutes, A “Welcome to UICcareers” message with instructions on how to access your account will be sent to your UIC email address. Follow the link to set up your password and log in. If you do not receive the welcome message within an hour, please call the Career Services office at 312-996-2300 for assistance.  *In order to apply to jobs, you need to fill out the required information on your UICcareers.com profile and upload your resume.        If I graduated over a year ago, may I still use UICcareers.com?         FAQ2a        If you have not set up a UICcareers.com account previously or your account is no longer accessible, you may request that your account be set up or reinstated.  Please complete the UICcareers.com access form to request and regain access to UICcareers.com .                     About    Back to main content           Hours & Location    Our Services    Contact Us    Staff Directory     Career Peer Mentors      Other Career Centers    Newsletters & Recorded Webinars    Frequently Asked Questions                  UIC Logo        Career Services         Students    Career Planning Guide    Make an Appointment    FAQs      Employers    Post a Position    UICcareers.com      Campus Partners    Campus Partners    Program/Workshop Request Forms        Footer Menu    Career Programs and Events    UICcareers    UIC Student Employment Office         Contact   Suite 3050 1200 West Harrison Chicago, IL 60607  Phone: (312) 996-2300  Fax: (312) 413-0383  careerservices@uic.edu        Social Media Accounts    Facebook    Twitter    YouTube             UIC.edu links   UIC.edu  Academic Calendar